org.jmisb.api.video

Interface IVideoStreamOutput

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    VideoStreamOutput

    @Beta
public interface IVideoStreamOutput
extends AutoCloseable
    Interface for writing video/metadata to a UDP/IP network stream.

    It is the caller's responsibility to enqueue frames at a rate on average equal to the frame rate specified in the stream's VideoOutputOptions, and set the PTS values of the frames to provide timing information. The stream itself will output packets as soon as they are available from the encoder.

      • queueMetadataFrame

        void queueMetadataFrame(MetadataFrame frame)
                 throws IOException
        Queue a MetadataFrame for output.

        Note that metadata frames will be buffered internally based pts values. Queued metadata frames will be sent once a video frame with greater or equal pts has been sent.

        Parameters:
        frame - The metadata frame to send
        Throws:
        IOException - if the stream could not be written
